      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Counting Tiles Strategy in Scrabble — Track What's Left to Win</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>7 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Every competitive Scrabble player shares one habit: they know what's left in the bag. Tile counting — the practice of tracking played letters throughout the game — transforms guesswork into informed strategy. When you know the blanks are gone, the last S just played, or that your opponent must be holding the Q, every decision from exchanges to endgame becomes sharper. Here's how to build this skill from scratch.</p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Core Principle</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">KNOWLEDGE = POWER</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">100 tiles. Track them all. Own the endgame.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Players who track tiles gain an estimated 15-25 points per game from better decision-making alone — without learning a single new word.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 1: What Is Tile Tracking? -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What Is Tile Tracking?</h2>

      <p>Tile tracking is the systematic practice of recording which letters have been played on the board during a game. By maintaining a running count of used tiles, you can calculate exactly what remains in the bag at any point — and in the endgame, deduce your opponent's entire rack.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Why It Works</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Scrabble uses a <span class="text-white font-medium">fixed, known set of 100 tiles</span>. Unlike card games where shuffled decks create uncertainty, every tile in Scrabble is public information once played. Tracking simply means paying attention to what's already visible.</p>
      </div>

      <p>Think of it like counting cards in blackjack — except it's completely legal and encouraged. The board is your open ledger. Every word played reveals information. The question is whether you're recording it or ignoring it.</p>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">100</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Total tiles</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">27</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Unique letters + blank</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">187</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Total point value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15-25</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Extra pts/game from tracking</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2: The Tally Sheet Method -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Tally Sheet Method — How to Track</h2>

      <p>Tournament players use a pre-printed tally sheet listing every tile and its count. As each word is played, they cross off the letters used. You can replicate this with a simple grid on paper or even mentally for key tiles.</p>

      <!-- Numbered Steps -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 How to Start Tracking</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-white">Print a tally sheet</strong> — list all 26 letters plus blanks with their starting counts (e.g., A×9, B×2, C×2... Blank×2).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-white">After each turn</strong> — cross off every letter played on the board (both your plays and your opponent's).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-white">Count remaining</strong> — at any point, subtract crossed tiles from the starting count to know what's still available.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-white">Verify your count</strong> — periodically add up: tiles on board + tiles in your rack + tiles in bag should always equal 100.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Full Tile Distribution Table -->
      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Letter</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Count</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Letter</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Count</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
