          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">A</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">9</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">N</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">6</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">B</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">O</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">8</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">C</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">P</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">3</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">D</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">4</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">Q</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-amber-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">10</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">E</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">12</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">R</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">6</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">F</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">S</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-amber-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">G</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">3</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">T</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">6</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">H</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">U</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">4</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">I</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">9</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">V</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">J</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-amber-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">W</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">K</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">X</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-amber-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">8</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">L</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">4</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">Y</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">M</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">Z</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-amber-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">10</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-2" colspan="3"></td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold">Blank</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-amber-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">0</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3: What Information Tracking Gives You -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What Tile Tracking Reveals</h2>

      <p>Once you maintain a running tally, several layers of strategic information become available to you — information your non-tracking opponent simply doesn't have.</p>

      <!-- Pill Badges: Key tiles to always track -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">Blank</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">×2</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">S</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">×4</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">Z</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">×1</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">Q</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">×1</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">X</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">×1</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">J</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">×1</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <!-- Purple Strategy Tiles -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Blank awareness:</span> Know whether 0, 1, or 2 blanks remain. If both are played, no opponent can bingo with a blank — you can relax your defensive posture.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">S tile management:</span> With only 4 S tiles total, knowing how many remain tells you the probability of hook plays and parallel extensions from your opponent.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Power tile status:</span> If Z, X, J are all played, no one can score 8-10 points from a single letter anymore. This changes the pace and scoring ceiling of the remaining game.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Exchange decisions:</span> Never exchange hoping for tiles that are already gone. Your tally tells you if the letters you need actually remain in the bag.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4: Rack Deduction -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Using Tracking for Opponent Rack Deduction</h2>

      <p>The most powerful application of tile counting is deducing your opponent's rack — especially in the endgame. Once the bag is empty, simple subtraction reveals everything.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🔬 The Math</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200"><span class="text-white font-medium">Opponent's rack</span> = 100 total tiles − tiles on board − tiles in your rack − tiles in bag.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-2">When the bag is empty: opponent's tiles = 100 − board tiles − your rack. Perfect information.</p>
      </div>

      <p>Even before the bag empties, partial deduction is powerful. If you've tracked 3 of the 4 S tiles on the board and have none yourself, there's exactly 1 S between the bag and your opponent's rack. This narrows the threat space dramatically.</p>

      <!-- Comparison Cards -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Tracking Player</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Knows opponent holds Q with no U available. Blocks the QI spot. Forces a -10 point penalty at game end.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Non-Tracking Player</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Doesn't realize Q is unseen. Leaves triple-letter + QI open. Opponent dumps Q for 62 points on the final turn.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Dig Deeper: Inline Cross-Links -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/tile-tracking-guide/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Tile Tracking Guide — Step-by-step system for counting every tile</span>
