          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 5: Endgame Perfect Play -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Endgame Perfect Play with Tracking</h2>

      <p>The endgame is where tile counting pays its biggest dividends. Once the bag is empty, a tracking player operates with complete information — they know every single tile on their opponent's rack. This transforms the last 3-5 turns from guesswork into a solvable puzzle.</p>

      <!-- Insight Callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 The Endgame Advantage</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">When you know your opponent's exact tiles, you can calculate their <span class="text-white font-medium">best possible play on every open spot</span> — then block the highest-scoring one while maximizing your own score. This is how tournament players consistently close out wins.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Block their hotspots:</span> If you know they hold a V and an open triple-word is adjacent to a vowel, that's their target. Play there first — even for fewer points — to deny them 30+.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Force the penalty:</span> If their tiles are unplayable (consonant-heavy, Q without U), keep the board closed. They'll be stuck passing or playing for minimal points while you control tempo.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Go out first:</span> Playing all your tiles before your opponent means they subtract their remaining tile values from their score and add them to yours. In tight games, this 10-20 point swing decides everything.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat Strip: Endgame value -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10-20</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Point swing from going out first</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3-5</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Final turns with perfect info</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">100%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Rack visibility when bag empty</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

